commit.message:
Deprecate Application-Specific Main Entrypoint Attributes

Issue a deprecation warning in Swift 5 and an error in Swift 6 when we encounter @UIApplicationMain and @NSApplicationMain. These attributes are unnecessary now that @main works with UIApplicationDelegate and NSApplicationDelegate. As these conformances are required when working with the corresponding attributes, we can migrate users off of them by replacing them with @main.

[Completion] Addd constructors from the completion cache back

31dee1ce1cb2ec339b39245e5f1601881f8e120c refactored the completion
filter, accidentally dropping initializers when found from the cache.
Add these back in and also modify the existing test to load from the
cache as well.

Resolves rdar://107807707.

Sema: Skip storage diagnostic for `@exclusivity` in swiftinterfaces.

Relax the diagnostics for the `@exclusivity` attribute in order to avoid type
checking failures for `public private(set)` properties in resilient libraries.
In a `swiftinterface` it's not possible to tell reliably whether a property has
storage.

Resolves rdar://107770440
NFC: Fix typos in SILGen test for @exclusivity.

Only return macros that are valid in their current position, ie. an
attached macro is not valid on a nominal.

Also return freestanding expression macros in code block item position
and handle the new freestanding code item macros.

Resolves rdar://105563583.
